160
00:11:12,601 --> 00:11:14,444
At the station no later than 10:30.

161
00:11:14,548 --> 00:11:15,765
And don't be late.

162
00:11:15,869 --> 00:11:17,120
This thing is supposed to go down at 11:00.

163
00:11:17,224 --> 00:11:19,309
Hey, and tell Diane I'm sorry and I'll

164
00:11:19,414 --> 00:11:21,152
make it up to you guys.

165
00:11:21,257 --> 00:11:23,168
Yeah.

166
00:11:23,272 --> 00:11:24,976
I'm sure she'll understand.

167
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:27,895
She's wonderful.

168
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,319
Understand what?

169
00:11:29,423 --> 00:11:30,397
I don't understand crap.

170
00:11:30,501 --> 00:11:31,510
Give me that phone.

171
00:11:31,614 --> 00:11:32,448
BILL: It's too late.

172
00:11:32,552 --> 00:11:34,221
He hung up.

173
00:11:34,324 --> 00:11:35,750
You're not going out tonight.

174
00:11:35,855 --> 00:11:38,495
BILL: Just let me tell you what's going on, OK?

175
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,650
You're not going out of here.

176
00:11:40,755 --> 00:11:42,632
You remember BR, don't you?

177
00:11:42,736 --> 00:11:44,161
DIANE: Yes.

178
00:11:44,266 --> 00:11:46,490
You remember when he told us his definition of a friend?

179
00:11:49,236 --> 00:11:52,328
He said that a friend was someone that you could call

180
00:11:52,433 --> 00:11:54,449
at 3:00 in the morning and say, meet me on the worst

181
00:11:54,553 --> 00:11:56,604
corner of town and bring a gun, and they'd show up,

182
00:11:56,709 --> 00:11:58,899
no questions asked.

183
00:11:59,003 --> 00:12:01,783
Neil is the only person I know who would do anything for me,

184
00:12:01,887 --> 00:12:04,251
no questions asked.

185
00:12:04,354 --> 00:12:08,039
So what's your definition of a wife?

186
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:10,472
Somebody who will put up with this BS?

187
00:12:10,576 --> 00:12:14,295
Somebody who will go along without complaining?

188
00:12:14,399 --> 00:12:18,883
Bill, don't you see?

189
00:12:18,988 --> 00:12:20,830
