212
00:13:32,290 --> 00:13:33,785
What?

213
00:13:33,889 --> 00:13:36,357
I said, you put the ring in a safe place, right?

214
00:13:36,461 --> 00:13:37,990
I don't know what you're taking about.

215
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:45,081
I said, you put the ring in a safe place, right?

216
00:13:45,184 --> 00:13:47,618
Yes, I put the ring in a safe place.

217
00:13:47,723 --> 00:13:51,511
And yes, I rented my tux, and yes, I paid for the wedding.

218
00:13:51,615 --> 00:13:52,518
[kiss]

219
00:13:54,848 --> 00:13:56,306
I just don't want anything to go wrong.

220
00:13:56,411 --> 00:13:57,836
That's all.

221
00:13:57,940 --> 00:14:00,860
I mean, this wedding means so much to Diane and to me.

222
00:14:00,964 --> 00:14:02,911
It's one of those things you only do one time in your life.

223
00:14:03,016 --> 00:14:07,082
So it might as well be right, right?

224
00:14:07,186 --> 00:14:09,445
Hey, man, are you getting any of this?

225
00:14:09,549 --> 00:14:10,418
Yeah.

226
00:14:10,522 --> 00:14:14,311
Yeah, I hear you.

227
00:14:14,415 --> 00:14:18,969
Listen, Bill, I know I really screwed stuff up for you

228
00:14:19,073 --> 00:14:20,880
and Diane tonight.

229
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:22,270
I'm sorry.

230
00:14:22,374 --> 00:14:27,971
She'll get over it, I hope.

231
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:32,523
This is going to make you a big hero.

232
00:14:32,628 --> 00:14:33,497
She'll be proud of you.

233
00:14:44,549 --> 00:14:45,384
Bingo.

234
00:14:48,895 --> 00:14:51,640
Looks like Lanky Louis set us straight.

235
00:15:05,369 --> 00:15:06,969
Ammo clips, fully loaded.

236
00:15:11,034 --> 00:15:13,920
Neil, what have we stumbled onto here?

237
00:15:14,024 --> 00:15:17,291
Another ad scam.

238
00:15:17,395 --> 00:15:18,298
I don't know.

239
00:15:21,218 --> 00:15:26,083
There's enough firepower here to destroy half the city.

240
00:15:26,188 --> 00:15:29,072
I think we better call for backup.

241
00:15:29,176 --> 00:15:30,290
[electric sound]

242
00:15:52,881 --> 00:15:55,906
Is, uh, is it clear?

243
00:15:56,010 --> 00:15:58,269
Get to it.

244
00:15:58,373 --> 00:16:00,772
Yes, um, I--

245
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:04,837
well, everything looks secure.

246
00:16:04,942 --> 00:16:08,488
I suppose I'll start with the inventory.

247
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:10,538
We're waiting.

248
00:16:10,642 --> 00:16:13,215
[music playing]

249
00:16:47,729 --> 00:16:49,188
The driver's getting nervous.

250
00:16:49,292 --> 00:16:50,717
He wants to know how much longer.

251
00:16:53,255 --> 00:16:56,000
You tell that chickenshit if you don't stop asking

252
00:16:56,104 --> 00:16:58,573
stupid questions, he won't be able to get

253
00:16:58,677 --> 00:17:01,388
a job driving a garbage truck.

254
00:17:01,492 --> 00:17:04,690
After I finished with him, he won't be able to walk.

255
00:17:04,794 --> 00:17:05,698
Got that?

256
00:17:05,802 --> 00:17:07,679
Yes, sir.

257
00:17:07,783 --> 00:17:09,764
[music playing]

258
00:17:53,036 --> 00:17:54,010
TERRORIST: Come on.

259
00:17:54,114 --> 00:17:55,469
let's move it.

260
00:17:55,574 --> 00:17:57,729
I want this stuff loaded and rolling in 10 minutes.

261
00:18:15,663 --> 00:18:17,680
Maybe this is some of the Libyan terrorists we've

262
00:18:17,784 --> 00:18:19,834
been hearing so much about.

263
00:18:19,938 --> 00:18:23,588
They're not speaking with an accent.

264
00:18:23,693 --> 00:18:27,967
Maybe the Libyans are recruiting local talent.

265
00:18:28,071 --> 00:18:28,904
Maybe.

266
00:18:36,657 --> 00:18:39,472
You're holding up my men, Bill.

267
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:43,017
Yes, sir, I realize that, but there seems to be a problem.

268
00:18:56,954 --> 00:18:59,561
In addition to the missing hand grenades, one of the crates

269
00:18:59,667 --> 00:19:01,855
has been tampered with.

270
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:06,409
Two of the rifles are missing.

271
00:19:06,513 --> 00:19:08,494
